cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a new architecture for video action recognition that is lightweight and memory-friendly, while still achieving high accuracy. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper introduces a temporal aggregation module to model temporal dependencies in a video, which could also place it in the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. The use of deep subnets and compact subnets suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the reduction in computational costs, which could place it in the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
